Subject: [PATCH 00/13] platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: generic enablement,
 status LEDs, webcam, debugfs lockdown

This follow-up series extends the in-tree msi-wmi-platform driver on top of
Antheas Kapenekakis's "add fan curves/platform profile/tdp/battery limiting"
work with generic, capability-based enablement and three new user-facing
feature interfaces. It is hardware-tested on an MSI Stealth GS66 12UHS
(MS-16V5).

Patches 1-10 make the control features work generically across modern MSI
notebooks without a per-model register table: MS-16V5 support, firmware-resume
state restore, a runtime capability cache (the Get_Device presence bitmap plus
the WMI/EC ABI version), a feature-descriptor architecture with a two-pass
probe, and a control gate that mirrors MSI Center's own Features.IsSupport()
heuristic (MSI vendor + notebook/convertible chassis + interface v2 + a
Tigerlake+ EC), plus a disable_control escape hatch and review fixes.

Patches 11-13 add new interfaces, all through the bounded Get_Data/Set_Data EC
ABI -- a single named register per call, not arbitrary EC access:

 - status/USB/keyboard LEDs as LED class devices (mic-mute, mute, USB backlight
   and the keyboard-backlight enable);

 - a webcam power control (camera_power), gated by the Get_Device
   SupportedWebCam bit.  On these machines it cuts power to the camera at the
   USB level -- the device de-enumerates from the bus rather than blanking the
   image -- so it is a writable control like ideapad-laptop's camera_power, not
   an SW_CAMERA_LENS_COVER switch (there is no physical cover);

 - and, since the debugfs interface can drive Set_EC() and friends (arbitrary
   EC / hardware-register writes, functionally /dev/mem-equivalent), a lockdown
   guard so the debug interface is refused under kernel lockdown (Secure Boot).

Hardware-tested on MS-16V5: the LED writes reach the EC, camera_power
enumerates/de-enumerates the integrated USB webcam, and platform_profile, the
charge threshold and the fan curves are unaffected. checkpatch --strict clean.

Florian Hänel (13):
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: add MS-16V5 (Stealth GS66 12Ux) quirk
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: restore state on firmware resume
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: fix uninitialized err in profile_setup
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: add runtime capability cache + Get_Device probe
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: feature-descriptor architecture + two-pass probe
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: rename quirk table to model
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: gate control by a runtime heuristic
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: fix issues found in review
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: add a disable_control module parameter
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: fix debugfs writes executing stale data
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: add status/USB/keyboard LEDs
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: add webcam power control
  platform/x86: msi-wmi-platform: lock down debugfs EC access

